    "description": "Encapsulate a fully-configured agent in a reusable BoxLang class.",
    "guidance": "For production applications, define agents as BoxLang classes that extend AiAgent. This approach gives you:\n\n• Reusability — instantiate anywhere with new agents.OrderAgent()\n• Organization — agent logic lives in its own file\n• Testability — unit test the agent config with TestBox\n• Inheritance — create a base company agent class, then specialize it\n• Lifecycle hooks — override init() for complex setup\n\nThe pattern:\n1. Class extends bxModules.bxai.models.runnables.AiAgent\n2. Override init() and call super.init() with your config\n3. Register tools, configure memory, set policies in private methods\n4. Instantiate with new agents.MyAgent() and call .run()\n\nFor app-wide agents (created once at startup), combine with the Agent Registry pattern (sample 023) to register and resolve named agents.",
    "output": "Order Status Report:\n\n✅ Order ORD-77123 is confirmed and being prepared for shipment.\n\nDetails:\n- Items: BoxLang Enterprise License (×1)\n- Order Date: 2024-01-15\n- Status: Processing → Expected to ship within 24 hours\n- Estimated Delivery: January 18-20\n\nWould you like me to set up a shipping notification? I can also check if expedited shipping is available for this order.",
    "docsUrl": "https://ai.ortusbooks.com/main-components/agents/class-based-agents.md",
